The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR) protocols for distributed storage systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of linear codes in the storage system suggests coding theory (cs.CR) and error-correcting codes (cs.CC) as relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the capacity-achieving properties of certain codes, which could fall under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
